id: pm-jhg9
title: Linked-test item reference parser skips item IDs after value-bearing flags
description: The SDK linked-command detector can treat option values such as json or 10 as the first positional token and miss the actual item ID in valid forms like pm get --format json pm-dead and pm history --limit 10 pm-dead.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags: []
created_at: "2026-07-15T17:30:28.900Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-15T17:50:51.123Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-15T17:50:28.811Z"
author: codex-root
acceptance_criteria: "Linked-test reference extraction skips every recognized value-bearing option before the single item positional, preserves boolean and inline-value forms, avoids classifying pm-shaped option values as the item, and has exact regression coverage."
parent: pm-oxrw
resolution: "The SDK parser now uses command-specific and global option arity to locate the single item positional; the redundant CLI import and obsolete suppression were removed, and the strict suppression budget was reduced to 158."
expected_result: "Valid item-referencing commands retain their item ID when value-bearing flags appear before it, including pm-shaped option values, with all analyzers and exact coverage green."
actual_result: "Greptile reproductions now return the intended item ID, DeepScan defect 230752438 is eliminated, focused tests pass 109 assertions across parser and release contracts, packed-package validation is clean, and the full 5,736-test suite is 100/100/100/100."
