comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-15T17:30:28.900Z",codex-root,"Duplicate check: searched all statuses for linked command value flags positional item format limit; no existing item describes this final hosted Greptile finding. Canonical lineage is the closed SDK governance feature pm-oxrw and the review correction belongs to PR #568."
  "2026-07-15T17:38:17.054Z",codex-root,"Review evidence: hosted Greptile correctly reproduced value-bearing flags before item positionals on c2d00316. DeepScan public API defect 230752438 reports the only new issue as UNUSED_IMPORT for extractReferencedPmItemIdsFromCommand in src/cli/commands/test.ts; it is already re-exported directly and the local import is redundant. Both findings are actionable in this item."
  "2026-07-15T17:50:20.360Z",codex-root,"Final evidence: contract-driven item positional parsing covers value-bearing global and command options, pm-shaped option values, inline values, booleans, and option terminators. DeepScan defect 230752438 is removed with its obsolete ESLint suppression, and the suppression ceiling is ratcheted to 158. Focused linked tests passed 60/60; release-contract tests passed 49/49; full suite passed 291 files and 5,736 tests with exact 100% statements, branches, functions, and lines. Strict lint, jscpd zero clones, 100% docstrings, SDK/package boundaries, and token budgets pass. Packed unbrained-pm-cli-2026.7.14.tgz acceptance created two real items, linked a pm get --format json command, and validate reported exactly one known reference and zero stale references."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-15T17:50:20.971Z",codex-root,"Linked-command reference parsing must honor option arity before the single item positional; scanning for the first non-dash token confuses flag values, while scanning for the first pm-shaped token confuses pm-shaped metadata values. Keep the value-flag contract synchronized with core help and ratchet suppressions whenever analyzer cleanup makes one obsolete."
